# Discussion continuity (project progress log)

Discussions in this repo are **project progress**. Do not treat them as disposable.

## New chat / context full (critical)

A **new Cursor chat does not automatically load the old chat window**.
Continuity comes from **files in this repo**, not from magic memory of the prior UI thread.

**At the start of a new conversation** in this repo (or when the user says recall / continue / what did we decide):

1. **Read** [`docs/DISCUSSION_LOG.md`](docs/DISCUSSION_LOG.md) first.
2. If they need more depth, open the linked `DISCUSSION_HISTORY_*.md` and/or `docs/lessons/`.
3. Only dig into `docs/transcripts/*.jsonl` if they ask for the full raw chat.

Answer from those files — do not pretend you still have the vanished chat buffer.

## Always-on habit (no user reminder required)

When a chat includes **decisions, architecture verdicts, PE locks, live HYSYS results, or “we agreed to…”**:

1. **Update** [`docs/DISCUSSION_LOG.md`](docs/DISCUSSION_LOG.md) — short bullets only (newest session at top).
2. Include: date, topic tags, decisions, open questions, pointers to lessons/trials if any.
3. If the session is substantial (architecture, live test, multi-topic), also add/update a dated file `docs/DISCUSSION_HISTORY_YYYY-MM-DD.md` (or `_pm` / `_night` suffix if same day already exists).
4. Prefer **simple markdown** — not dumping full chat JSON into the log.
5. Before this chat hits context limits, prefer updating the log early so a new chat can continue.

## Raw transcripts

- Cursor keeps full chats under the local agent-transcripts cache (may stay on this PC only).
- To put a copy **inside the git repo** (survives new chat / other PC after push):
  `scripts/archive_discussion_transcript.py`
- Index: [`docs/transcripts/README.md`](docs/transcripts/README.md).

## Do not

- Wait for the user to say “please record this.”
- Claim you “remember the old chat window” without reading DISCUSSION_LOG.
- Replace Inventory / coded Assist with chat opinions.
- Paste entire transcripts into DISCUSSION_LOG (keep the log thin).

